cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.CL, cs.GR 

The paper deals with explaining the decisions of neural networks in the visual domain, specifically in the context of a visual question answering benchmark. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also proposes metrics to evaluate explanations, which suggests that it may also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and natural language processing (cs.CL) sub-categories. Finally, the paper deals with 3D shapes, which suggests that it may also belong to the graphics (cs.GR) sub-category.
